            <link>https://grauds.github.io/clematis.doc/blog/gradle-update-post</link>
            <guid>https://grauds.github.io/clematis.doc/blog/gradle-update-post</guid>
            <pubDate>Sat, 24 May 2025 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[The Palantir Docker Plugin is now EOL, which probably is the old news,]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The <a href="https://github.com/palantir/gradle-docker" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Palantir Docker Plugin</a> is now EOL, which probably is the old news,
however, the worse part is that it is waiting to be updated for Gradle 8.12 and up:
<a href="https://github.com/palantir/gradle-docker/issues/801" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://github.com/palantir/gradle-docker/issues/801</a>.</p>
<p>Some Clematis APIs are dependent on the plugin, so looking for workarounds or removal.</p>]]></content:encoded>
            <category>maintenance</category>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[New Pet Projects Ideas]]></title>
            <link>https://grauds.github.io/clematis.doc/blog/new-ideas-post</link>
            <guid>https://grauds.github.io/clematis.doc/blog/new-ideas-post</guid>
            <pubDate>Thu, 20 Mar 2025 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[Throwing in some stuff to experiment with:]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Throwing in some stuff to experiment with:</p>
<ol>
<li>Backends for Frontends (BFF): we need some aggregation to
build the next web application, Clematis Day.
Will probably be using <a href="https://bff-patterns.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://bff-patterns.com</a>.</li>
<li>Use <a href="https://storybook.js.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Storybook</a> to build the next
web application.</li>
<li>Use <a href="https://headlessui.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Headless UI</a> in the next web application to
get a feeling of how to be ready for any UIKit.</li>
<li>Add ML/Deep Learning to Clematis Weather API to select a weather picture.</li>
</ol>]]></content:encoded>
            <category>Idea</category>
        </item>
